id=acc
domain=vr25
name=Advanced Charging Controller (ACC)
version=v2025.5.18-stable
versionCode=202505187
author=VR25 (community stable)
description=[community STABLE (fix2-fix12 consolidated + hardened): charge limit holds EXACTLY at your level on Pixel/Tensor, no overshoot (driven by the target level on both sides, never "charge to 100 then interrupt"); default discharges down to the limit then HOLDS there (battery-idle), or cycles to the lower limit when idle is off; allow_idle_above_pcap defaults false (never sit above the limit); settings apply within ~1s; daemon survives front-end restarts; fail-safe on every capacity/temp limit + breach watchdog; scanner can LOCK a chosen method. fix9: full fail-safe coverage + flat-hold on all charge-limit nodes + breach watchdog. fix8: malformed-config fail-safe + locked-switch recovery. fix7: Pixel/Tensor cap now HOLDS at the limit. Drives the google charge_stop_level node to pause_capacity so the firmware holds the battery flat at the cap (tight, no overshoot, true idle) instead of toggling 100/5 and sawtoothing past it; switch scanner prefers idle/flat-hold switches; restores retry-on-stall (no daemon re-init mid-pause). Includes fix2-fix6.] Extend your battery's service life by controlling charging current, temperature, and voltage. Any root solution is supported. The installation is always "systemless". Works on Android and KaiOS.
updateJson=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/VR-25/acc/master/module.json
